article.headline: N. Dakota St. 73, Ind.-Pur.-Ft. Wayne 57
article.story: FARGO, N.D. (AP) -- Brett Winkelman scored 18 points and Ben Woodside and Mike Nelson added 17 each as North Dakota State won its 11th straight home game, 73-57 over Indiana University-Purdue University Fort Wayne. With the win, the Bison (20-8) reached the 20-win plateau for the first time since moving to NCAA Division I. They also set a team record with five blocked shots, giving them 136 for the season. Winkelmann and Andre Smith had double-doubles for NDSU. Winkelmann had 10 rebounds and Smith scored 13 points and grabbed 14 rebounds. Smith also had four steals and four assists. The Bison shot just 36 percent in the first half, but they still managed to build a 34-21 lead thanks to a big edge in offensive rebounding. NDSU outrebounded IPFW 39-29. That included 17 offensive boards. IPFW (12-17) got 16 points from Jaraun Burrows and 13 from Chris Perkins.
